The trading in the shares of the listed entities may be suspended on non-compliance with SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015 (LODR). Some of the relevant regulations are mentioned as under: 
  i. Failure to comply with regulation 17(1) of LODR with respect to board composition including appointment of woman director for two consecutive quarters;
  ii. Failure to comply with regulation 18(1) of LODR with respect to constitution of audit committee for two consecutive quarters.
  iii. Failure to comply with regulation 27(2) of LODR with respect to submission of corporate governance compliance report for two consecutive quarters;
  iv. Failure to comply with regulation 31(1) of LODR with respect to submission of shareholding pattern for two consecutive quarters;
  v. Failure to comply with regulation 33 of LODR with respect to submission of financial results for two consecutive quarters;
  vi. Failure to comply with regulation 34 of LODR with respect to submission of Annual Report for two consecutive financial years;
  vii. Failure to submit information on the reconciliation of shares and capital audit report, for two consecutive quarters;
  viii. Receipt of the notice of suspension of trading of that entity by any other recognized stock exchange on any or all of the above grounds.

  Further, the details regarding the suspended companies may be checked on the website of Stock Exchanges i.e. BSE (<a href="https://www.bseindia.com/static/corporates/SEBI_SOP_circular.html)" target="_blank">https://www.bseindia.com/static/corporates/SEBI_SOP_circular.html)</a> and NSE (<a href="https://www.nseindia.com/regulations/listing-compliance/non-compliant-companies-list)" target="_blank">https://www.nseindia.com/regulations/listing-compliance/non-compliant-companies-list)</a>
